s of various intellectual property court cases, Jessica Silbey examines the experiences of everyday creators and innovators navigating ownership, sharing, and sustainability within the internet eco-system and current IP laws. Crucially, the book encourages refiguring the substance of "progress" and the function of intellectual property in terms that demonstrate the urgency of art and science to social justice today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLAW / Intellectual Property / General.2bisacsh  aIntellectual property.  aconstitutional law.  acopyright.  adistributive justice.  aequality.  ainternet.  apatent.  aprecarity.  aprivacy.  atrademark.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2022 Englishz978311099300408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2022z9783110993011oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107664860 cprintz978150360830640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363192240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503631922423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503631922/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099300-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022